bug.author: philipphenkel
bug.summary: What's the license of pre-trained TensorFlow.js models?
bug.description:
I want to use tfjs-models in a commercial application. While source code in the <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tfjs-models>tfjs-models repository</denchmark-link> is licensed under Apache 2.0, I did not find any info about the license of the models hosted on storage.googleapis.com. For example <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tfjs-models/tree/master/body-pix>body-pix</denchmark-link> is loading its model from <denchmark-link:https://storage.googleapis.com/tfjs-models>storage.googleapis.com/tfjs-models</denchmark-link>
e.g. <denchmark-link:https://storage.googleapis.com/tfjs-models/savedmodel/posenet_mobilenet_025_partmap/model.json>posenet_mobilenet_025_partmap/model.json</denchmark-link>
<denchmark-link:https://storage.googleapis.com/tfjs-models/savedmodel/posenet_mobilenet_025_partmap/tensorflowjs_model.pb>posenet_mobilenet_025_partmap/tensorflowjs_model.p</denchmark-link>
<denchmark-link:https://storage.googleapis.com/tfjs-models/savedmodel/posenet_mobilenet_025_partmap/weights_manifest.json>posenet_mobilenet_025_partmap/weights_manifest.json</denchmark-link>
Are the files on <denchmark-link:https://storage.googleapis.com/tfjs-models>storage.googleapis.com/tfjs-models</denchmark-link> licensed under Apache 2.0 as well? If yes, it would be great to document it, and I'm willing to submit a PR.

comments.comment: The <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tfjs-models/blob/master/LICENSE>Apache 2.0 license</denchmark-link> has been added to the TensorFlow.js models repo. Am closing this issue; thank you for the request!
